2.1 Alphabet & file format (exact)

Allowed characters in source file: the character 1 (U+0031) and newline \n.

A source file is a sequence of lines. Each non-empty line L contains a contiguous run of 1 characters of length k ≥ 1 (no spaces, no other characters). Empty lines are not allowed (assembler error).

