2.2 Mathematical decoding (exact)

Let the infinite list of primes be p1 = 2, p2 = 3, p3 = 5, p4 = 7, p5 = 11, ....

Given a line length k compute its Gödel decomposition:

Let N := k (the positive integer encoded by the run of 1).

Factor N uniquely into prime powers:

N = ∏_{i=1..t} p_i^{e_i},     with each e_i ≥ 0 and p_i the i-th prime.


