Adds a new procedurally-generated QASM instruction (4 codepoints) using Arabic letters + Eastern numerals

Emits a small “reflection” paragraph that references checksums/timestamps (a mechanical self-recognition)

An RSS feed and sitemap are rebuilt every iteration

Option to start a local HTTP server to surf the site: python -m http.server --directory site 8000

Usage

Save the script below as qasm_site_grower.py.

Run (default infinite loop — stop with Ctrl+C):

python3 qasm_site_grower.py --out site


or limit iterations:

python3 qasm_site_grower.py --out site --max-iterations 100


Open site/index.html in a browser, or serve it:

python3 -m http.server --directory site 8000
# then visit http://localhost:8000

The script (single file)
#!/usr/bin/env python3
# qasm_site_grower.py
# Procedural QASM website generator that iteratively expands and "recognizes" its own content.
# Safe: local filesystem only. No network propagation. Run locally and stop with Ctrl+C.

import os, sys, time, argparse, hashlib, json, random, html
from datetime import datetime

